Package fi.abo.kogni.soile2.projecthandling.participant

Interface Participant

All Known Implementing Classes:
DBParticipant, ParticipantImpl, TokenParticipant
public interface Participant
This interface represents a participant as needed while running an experiment. An implementation of this interface needs to take care of STORING information on a Participant (e.g. result data), and retrieval of task-relevant data (e.g. outputs that might be needed by filters). It does NOT need to take care of retrieving other data of the participant, and thus doesn't need to store that data. We assume, that an instance of this Interface will be loaded at the beginning of a query. As such, it can be considered as unmutable during one call. When handling it, you need to ensure that it is refreshed if necessary if it has been changed.
Author:
Thomas Pfau

    • getValueForRandomizationGroup

      Object getValueForRandomizationGroup(String randomizerID)
      Get the Value that was assigned to this participant by a specific randomizer (if any is assigned). This will ensure, that if a a participant encounters a randomizer twice the value is not changed.
      Parameters:
      randomizerID - the ID of the randomizer
      Returns:
      The value that was saved for this specific randomizer. The randomizer needs to know what this value is and it has to be depositable in a JsonArray.
